    <h1>Top 5 Educational Movies and Latest Web Series with Insightful Knowledge</h1>

    <h2>Top 5 Educational Movies</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>
            12 Angry Men
            <ul>
                <li>Year: 1957</li>
                <li>Main Actors: Henry Fonda, Lee J. Cobb, Martin Balsam</li>
                <li>Description: A compelling courtroom drama that delves into the complexities of the American justice system and the importance of jury deliberation. It showcases the impact of personal biases and moral courage.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            A Beautiful Mind
            <ul>
                <li>Year: 2001</li>
                <li>Main Actors: Russell Crowe, Jennifer Connelly, Ed Harris</li>
                <li>Description: Based on the true story of mathematician John Nash, who battles schizophrenia while making significant contributions to game theory. The film highlights the challenges of mental illness and the power of perseverance.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            The Imitation Game
            <ul>
                <li>Year: 2014</li>
                <li>Main Actors: Benedict Cumberbatch, Keira Knightley, Matthew Goode</li>
                <li>Description: The film chronicles the life of Alan Turing, a brilliant mathematician who played a crucial role in breaking the Enigma code during World War II. It underscores Turing's impact on computer science and his personal struggles.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Hidden Figures
            <ul>
                <li>Year: 2016</li>
                <li>Main Actors: Taraji P. Henson, Octavia Spencer, Janelle Monáe</li>
                <li>Description: The inspiring story of three African-American women mathematicians who worked at NASA and were instrumental in the success of the early space missions. The film sheds light on their significant contributions and the fight for equality.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            The Theory of Everything
            <ul>
                <li>Year: 2014</li>
                <li>Main Actors: Eddie Redmayne, Felicity Jones, Tom Prior</li>
                <li>Description: A biographical film about the life of physicist Stephen Hawking, exploring his groundbreaking work in cosmology and his battle with ALS. The movie highlights Hawking's achievements and his extraordinary resilience.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Latest Web Series</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>
            The Bear (2022–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: This series revolves around a young chef from the fine dining world who comes home to run his family's sandwich shop after a death in the family. It's praised for its realistic depiction of the culinary industry and intense storytelling.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Wednesday (2022–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: A Tim Burton-directed series focusing on Wednesday Addams from "The Addams Family" as a student at Nevermore Academy. The show blends dark humor with a supernatural mystery.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            The Last of Us (2023–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Based on the popular video game, this series follows the journey of Joel and Ellie across a post-apocalyptic United States. It has been noted for its emotional depth and faithful adaptation.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Succession (2018–2023)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Although not brand new, its final season recently concluded. This series follows the Roy family, owners of a global media empire, and their internal power struggles. It's known for its sharp writing and complex characters.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            The Sandman (2022–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Adapted from Neil Gaiman’s acclaimed comic series, this fantasy series follows Dream, one of the Endless, as he navigates through various realms and encounters. It has been praised for its visual style and faithful adaptation.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Severance (2022–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: This series explores a dystopian workplace where employees undergo a procedure to sever their work and personal memories. It's noted for its unique premise and intriguing exploration of work-life balance.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Heartstopper (2022–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Based on the graphic novels by Alice Oseman, this coming-of-age series follows two teenage boys who fall in love while navigating high school. It's celebrated for its heartfelt and inclusive storytelling.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Shadow and Bone (2021–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Adapted from Leigh Bardugo's Grishaverse novels, this fantasy series explores a world divided by darkness and follows a young woman discovering her extraordinary powers.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            The White Lotus (2021–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: This anthology series focuses on the lives of guests and staff at a luxurious resort, with each season exploring different themes and characters. It's known for its dark comedy and social commentary.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba (2019–present)
            <ul>
                <li>Description: Although originally an anime, its latest seasons continue to gain international popularity. It follows a young boy fighting demons to save his sister and find a cure for his family.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
